LIBREVILLE, GABON Burkina Faso scored an upset 2-0 win over Tunisia in their Africa Cup of Nations quarterfinal match in Libreville, Gabon, on Saturday.With the sides heading towards extra time, substitute Aristide Bancen broke the deadlock in the 80th minute from a free kick on the edge of the area.With Tunisia pushing intensely for an equaliser, they were caught on the break and Niguimbe Nakoulma converted in front of an open goal to seal the match as a contest in the 84th minute.Africa News Agency